Title: Saving Babies? Revisiting the effect of very low birth weight classification 
Abstract:
 We reconsider the effect of very low birth weight classification on infant
 mortality. We demonstrate that the estimates are highly sensitive to the
 exclusion of observations in the immediate vicinity of the 1,500-g
 threshold, weakening the confidence in the results originally reported in
 Almond, Doyle, Kowalski, and Williams (2010).  Copyright 2011, Oxford University Press.
